Installing @{b}HWUpdate@{ub}
*******************

@{b}HWUpdate@{ub} couldn't be easier to install.  Just copy it somewhere on your
path for easy access.  I suggest that you put it in your CNet: directory,
but hey, it's your computer. ;-)

Oh, yeah.  You're going to need an NNTP/UUCP "ACTIVE" file, and you'll
need to have CNet installed.

@EndNode

@Node "Usage" "HWUpdate - Usage"
@Next "Thanks"
@Prev "Installation"
@Toc "Main"

Using @{b}HWUpdate@{ub}
**************

Command line template:
@{b}HWUpdate@{ub} <UUCP/NNTP "ACTIVE" file> [FORCE] [VERBOSE]

The first item on @{b}HWUpdate@{ub}'s command line must be the full-path
filename of your ACTIVE file.

The @{i}FORCE@{ui} keyword tells @{b}HWUpdate@{ub} to update the hiwater
marks in all of your UUCP subboards, whether they need it or not.  By
default, only the newsgroups with hiwater marks greater than 32767 get
updated.

The @{i}VERBOSE@{ui} option tells @{b}HWUpdate@{ub} to show you each base
it processes.  This option should be used until you are farmiliar with what
@{b}HWUpdate@{ub} is doing to your system.

---

@{b}HWUpdate@{ub} uses the "CDROM/Part0 Path" of your UUCP message bases to
locate the newsgroup.  If HWUpdate can't find a particular newsgroup, this
would be the best place to check.

Please note that @{b}HWUpdate@{ub} does not save the changes it makes.  It should be
run immediately before you start picking up new mail, for best results.

@EndNode

